## Dataset Provenance

TR-Gold-Morph v1 ({{ "{:,.0f}".format(metrics.dataset_v1_entries) }} tokens): manually validated annotations derived from BOUN Treebank and Zeyrek candidates. Tiers: gold (2,496 entries, linguist-verified), silver (78,041 entries, ensemble-confident).

TR-Gold-Morph v2 (2.5M target): pipeline ready; sources include OSCAR-tr (CC0/CC-BY-4.0), mC4-tr (ODC-BY), Wikipedia-tr (CC-BY-SA-3.0), BOUN Treebank (CC-BY-SA-4.0). IMST-UD (CC-BY-NC-SA-3.0) used only for internal evaluation — not included in the published dataset due to the NC clause.

Dataset: `melikkul/tr-gold-morph` (HuggingFace Datasets, pending v2 upload)

Source corpus manifest: `data/external/manifest.json`

License: CC BY 4.0 (main corpus). BOUN/Wikipedia-derived shards carry CC BY-SA. See [LICENSE-DATA](LICENSE-DATA).

## Limitations and Known Gaps

- **`em_argmax` vs `em_string`**: The {{ "%.1f"|format(metrics.em_argmax_ensemble * 100) }}% headline is candidate-index argmax accuracy (within-system). Cross-system comparable `em_string` (canonical-string equality) is pending the SLURM eval run; it may differ. Both metrics are reported in `models/v6/eval_results.json` after the run.
- **Manual annotation pool**: Gold tier currently 2,496 entries (1-annotator). Cohen's κ requires a 200-entry double-annotated overlap which is planned for the v2 build.
- **TTC-3600 classification**: The {{ "%.1f"|format(metrics.classification_macro_f1_atomized_berturk * 100) }}% F1 figure depends on dataset availability (Akın & Akın 2007, email-request). Results reported from the most recent run; see `audit/benchmark_results/` for the artifact.
- **BOUN ShareAlike**: BOUN UD treebank is CC-BY-SA-4.0. Model weights trained on BOUN-derived data should be distributed under CC-BY-SA-4.0. Shards are tracked separately in `data/external/manifest.json`.
- **Login-node benchmarks**: Zeyrek throughput ({{ metrics.zeyrek_tok_per_sec }} tok/s) was measured on the login node. Orfoz compute-node figure will be higher and will replace this value after the authoritative SLURM run.
- **OOV handling**: Zeyrek fails on neologisms (~4% of web-crawled Turkish). DualHead generator handles these but is 13pp below the disambiguator on the held-out set.

